# Playwright MCP runtime dirs (one per server mode).
# Each mode's output/ is gitignored; the persistent mode's profile/ too.
# config.json, README.md, and a .gitkeep inside each dir stay tracked so the
# folder structure is visible on a fresh clone.
playwright/headless/output/*
!playwright/headless/output/.gitkeep
playwright/interactive/output/*
!playwright/interactive/output/.gitkeep
playwright/tracing/output/*
!playwright/tracing/output/.gitkeep
playwright/persistent/output/*
!playwright/persistent/output/.gitkeep
playwright/persistent/profile/*
!playwright/persistent/profile/.gitkeep

# Ephemeral modes use isolated (in-memory) profiles and should never write to
# their profile/ dir — but ignore any contents defensively so that if isolation
# ever regresses, captured cookies/credentials can't be committed. The
# placeholder README.md in each stays tracked.
playwright/headless/profile/*
!playwright/headless/profile/README.md
playwright/interactive/profile/*
!playwright/interactive/profile/README.md
playwright/tracing/profile/*
!playwright/tracing/profile/README.md

# Launcher runtime state (lockfiles, log) - per-mode subdir created on demand.
playwright/headless/state/
playwright/interactive/state/
playwright/tracing/state/
playwright/persistent/state/

## Web publish staging (intermediate dir assembled by tools/publish-web/build.ps1; Web/site/ IS tracked)
Web/_staging/

## Dedicated server tree (see DedicatedServer/CLAUDE.md)
## Everything inside DedicatedServer/ is local-only except CLAUDE.md, the launcher
## script, the session-lock rules template, and source code under dev-plugins/.
## The active session.lock and the dev-plugins build outputs stay ignored.
/DedicatedServer/*
!/DedicatedServer/CLAUDE.md
!/DedicatedServer/dedicated-server.ps1
!/DedicatedServer/session.lock.template
!/DedicatedServer/dev-plugins/
/DedicatedServer/dev-plugins/**/bin/
/DedicatedServer/dev-plugins/**/obj/

